bush bread
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a damper cooked in ashes of an open fire or a basic loaf cooked in a camp oven.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date:  0/0/1849
Source:  Otago Journal
Author:
Vol / Page:  v/71
Edition:
Quote:  Dampers, that is flour and water mixed together ... and thrown on the ashes ...; this is bush bread and I had rather have it than any bread I ever tasted.
Notes:   (`A Settler')

Date:  14/4/1849
Source:  Letters from Otago
Author:
Vol / Page:  28
Edition:  1978
Quote:  We three act as cook week about, which allows our man more time to work and make dampers, that is, flour and water mixed together till it becomes a paste, and then thrown on the ashes where it bakes well; this is bush bread, and I had rather have it than any bread I ever tasted.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1988
